                                        "title": "",
                                        "description": "this is solid. like, actually usable, not just for show.\n\na few things i notice:\n￼\nfirst, the structure itself is right.\n\t•\t2 objectives only\n\t•\tclear separation: explore vs resolve\n\t•\teach kr is outcome-based\n\t•\tyou added a decision kr (huge)\n\nthis already puts you ahead of most okr setups.\n￼\nnow tightening a bit:\n\nobjective 1 (ideas)\n\nthis is mostly strong, but one tweak:\n\t•\tkr1 (autocomplete usable for me) → good, but slightly soft\nright now “usable” could still mean “barely works”\n\nyou might sharpen it to something like:\n\n“i use autocomplete in ≥2 real workflows without it breaking”\n\njust enough to force real usage, not just testing\n￼\n\t•\tkr2 (polymarket produces ≥1 genuine + usable signal) → good\ni’d just mentally define “usable” before you start, otherwise you’ll rationalize later\n￼\n\t•\tkr3 (≥10 qualified people engage meaningfully) → strong\nthis is your best kr. hard to fake.\n￼\n\t•\tkr4 (kill / continue / double down) → good, but like we talked about, this one depends on you enforcing honesty\n￼\nobjective 2 (kiki)\n\nthis is clean. you captured the branching really well.\n\nsmall notes:\n\t•\tkr1 (25 companies contacted, 2 convos) → good\nthis is one of the few places where effort-based is fine because it’s top-of-funnel\n\t•\tkr2 (decision by 4/25) → this is the most important kr on this whole board\nthis is what prevents drift\n\t•\tkr3 (no active support requests) → strong, very concrete\n\t•\tkr4 (inform users of outcome + timeline) → good\n\t•\tkr5 (no deal → subs canceled + 0 infra cost) → perfect closure kr\n￼\none thing to watch\n\nyou’ve set yourself up well, but the only way this fails is:\n\nyou hit kr1–3 partially and then hesitate on kr4 (decision)\n\neverything here is designed to funnel you into making a call. if you soften that, the whole system degrades.\n￼\noverall\n\nthis is tight.\n\t•\tnot bloated\n\t•\tnot performative\n\t•\tdirectly usable inside anchors\n\nif you actually run your anchors against this, you’ll get real signal in a week.\n\nthe only question left is execution discipline, not structure.",
